05/02/2004
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Turkish Parliamentary Speaker Bulent Arinc asked the EU Wednesday (4 February) to demonstrate a far-sighted approach in its policy towards Turkey and consider that having Turkey as a member would increase its potential influence on human rights, democracy and the rule of law in neighbouring countries. Arinc was speaking at the 16th conference of the European parliament president and parliament speakers of candidate countries.
In other news, Turkish Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul travels to Germany on Thursday for the Munich Security Policy Conference. He will attend a meeting of counterparts from other NATO countries. (Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 04/02/04)
